text: 2017 mural by Heesco at Weethalle, New South Wales Heesco (real name Khürelbaataryn Khosnaran, ) is a street artist based in Melbourne, Australia. Originally from Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia, he moved to Melbourne in 2010 and has painted various artworks around the area, including a massive mural depicting a woman in traditional Mongolian dress at the Victoria University campus in Footstray, winning the Footscray Art Prize for Street Art. ==References== ==External links== * Official Website * Category:Australian graffiti artists Category:Mongolian artists Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Mongolian emigrants to Australia Category:People from Ulaanbaatar Category:Artists from Melbourne
